Faculty Scholarly Productivity Index</link></group>
</social_group>
</university>
</body>
 listing for the top performing programs in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../618/587618.xml">
public administration</link> and 9th in the listing for the top performing programs in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../324/153324.xml">
public policy</link>.</p>
<p>

The Medical Management program was ranked 4th by Modern Healthcare Magazine in the 2006 rankings of the top business graduate schools for physician executives.</p>

